HEADWORD: Dully
<hw>Dul"ly</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>adv.</pos> <def>In a dull manner;
stupidly; slowly; sluggishly; without life or spirit.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>Supinely calm and <qex>dully</qex> innocent.</q> <rj><qau> G.
Lyttelton.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Dulocracy</ent>⟦br⟧
